<body>
SCCS Registration Policies (2011-2012)
<UL>
<LI> This year, school will group students based upon student needs. Parents can request, but it is the school that makes the decision. Please don not interrupt the school teaching plan by moving your kids around without any notice to the school.
<LI> Enrichment programs are registered annually for both the Fall and Spring terms: 
 <ul>
 <li>If you pick the Fall programs but not the Spring programs, the same programs in Spring as in Fall will be automatically added. <li>You can pick different programs in Fall and Spring. 
 <li>If you decide to drop classes, you should request cancellation and refund by contacting support@ynhchineseschool.org or by visiting school office.
 </ul>
<LI> For returning students, please just select enrichment classes. Language classes have been assigned for you based on your Chinese proficiency. 
<LI> New students will have the chance to pick grades/subjects but not classrooms.
<LI> The first day of school will be September 11. On that day, we just have Chinese Language classes. The enrichment programs will start on September 18, one week later.
<LI> Fees 
<pre>
    * Annual family membership (due in Fall): $20
    * Safety Patrol Deposit (refundable): $40
    * Annual Registration fee on or before September 18:  $20
    * Annual Registration fee after September 18:  $40 
    * Chinese language class (two terms): $260
    * General enrichment class: $80 per term, $160 per year
    * $25 is charged for bounced check
    * $10 late fee for Fall bill not paid before Sept 30 or Spring bill not paid before Jan 31
</pre>
<LI> Refund Policy
<pre>
    * Full refund of class fee before third lesson
    * No refund on or after the third lesson
    * Safety deposit is refunable after fulfilling all assigned duties
    * All other fees, such as the registration fee, late fee, etc. are not refundable
</UL>
